  "texts": [
    "In the case of forecasting, Y ∈ R t ′ ×d represents the same time series as X with a given delay, which can have the same length t or a different one.",
    "In the case of a classification problem, Y ∈ {1,..., c} represents the class of the time series, such as the type of activity of a signal (SMS, call, internet), where c is the number of classes.",
    "The dataset (x i, y i) n i=1 denotes the collection of observations of (X, Y) of size n. Let f be the prediction model mapping X to Y, and L: (X × Y) → R be a loss function based on the predictions errors (e.g., the mean squared error in regression, or the cross-entropy in classification).",
    "We focus in this study on deep neural network architectures f θ, where θ ∈ Θ denotes the weights of the neural network that are optimized through L: f θ * = arg min θ∈Θ L(X, Y).",
    "Gradient Norm Computation for Importance scoreTo identify important samples, we track per-sample gradient norms across all epochs."
  ],
